HEADWORD: Wretchless
<hw>Wretch"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Reckless</er>.]</ety>
<def>Reckless; hence, disregarded.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> --
<wordforms><wf>Wretch"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
-- <wf>Wretch"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark></wordforms> <rj><au>Bk. of Com.
Prayer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your deaf ears should listen⟦br⟧
Unto the <qex>wretchless</qex> clamors of the poor.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrey</ent>⟦br⟧
